##OpenSSL
###Description
The OpenSSL Project is a collaborative effort to develop a robust, commercial-grade, full-featured, and Open Source toolkit implementing the Secure Sockets Layer (SSL v2/v3) and Transport Layer Security (TLS v1) protocols as well as a full-strength general purpose cryptography library.
###Donation
[Donation page.](http://www.openssl.org/support/donations.html)
###Download
[Source](http://www.openssl.org/source/)
###Examples
From Grondilu's [post,](http://www.bitcoin.org/smf/index.php?topic=2458.msg33379#msg33379) to encrypt the wallet, from a terminal in bitcoin parent directory, type:

openssl enc -aes256 -in ./bitcoin/wallet.dat -out wallet.dat.aes256

From [Paul Heinlein's](http://www.madboa.com/people/paul/) [openssl command line how to,](http://www.madboa.com/geek/openssl/) to decode, add the '-d' option, set the '-in' option to the output file name, to type:

openssl enc -d -aes256 -in wallet.dat.aes256 -out wallet.dat
###FAQ
[FAQ](http://www.openssl.org/support/faq.html)
###HomePage
[OpenSSL Project](http://www.openssl.org)
